Package: blocklist
Title: Harvest Byte-References of Compressed Array Data Chunks Native to HDF5-Accessible Files 
Version: 0.0.1.9002
Authors@R: 
    person("Michael", "Sumner", , "mdsumner@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2471-7511"))
Description: Generate byte-reference stores from chunked array storage, on disk, on s3 storage or at urls. 
 Array sources are logically mosaiced with gdal multidimensional tool 'mdim mosaic' and this is used to 
 extract and organize raw byte references (path, offset, size) written to Parquet with semantic grouping of 
 manually-sharded, positionally-indexed parquet reference store. The structure is a directory of parquet files, manually partitioned 
 by variable (subdirectory) and by flat-chunk-index range ('refs.N.parq', 'record_size' rows each), with the partition keys 
 implied positionally rather than stored as columns (i.e. _not_ hive-encoded). This is compatible with "kerchunk-parquet Zarr", and 
 is used as an generic and intermediate convenience before generating 'icechunk' versions. 
